    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Finatra 2.1.1 Is Now Available!]]></title>
    <link href="http://finatra.info/finatra/blog/2015/10/29/finatra-2-dot-1-1-is-now-available/"/>
    <updated>2015-10-29T12:25:54-07:00</updated>
    <id>http://finatra.info/finatra/blog/2015/10/29/finatra-2-dot-1-1-is-now-available</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3>Finatra <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/releases/tag/v2.1.1">Release 2.1.1</a> is now available from <a href="http://search.maven.org/#search%7Cga%7C1%7Cg%3A%22com.twitter.finatra%22%20AND%20v%3A%222.1.0%22">Maven Central</a>.</h3>

<p>There are lots of improvements in this release. Please checkout the [v2.1.1] (<a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/releases/tag/v2.1.1">https://github.com/twitter/finatra/releases/tag/v2.1.1</a>) release tag on github for more information.</p>

<p>As always, you can download the release from <a href="http://search.maven.org/#search%7Cga%7C1%7Cg%3A%22com.twitter.finatra%22%20AND%20v%3A%222.1.0%22">Maven Central</a>.</p>

<h3>Our new <a href="http://finatra.info/finatra/finatra/user-guide">User Guide</a> is also now available!</h3>

<p>We&rsquo;ve been working hard to improve documentation and we&rsquo;re also happy to announce that our new <a href="http://finatra.info/finatra/finatra/user-guide">user guide</a> is out and available.</p>

<p>See the Finatra <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra">github page</a> or checkout our new <a href="http://finatra.info/finatra/finatra/user-guide">User Guide</a> for more information on getting started.</p>

<p>&ndash; The <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/finatra-users">Finatra</a> Team</p>
]]></content>
  </entry>
  
  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Finatra 2.1.0 Now Publicly Available]]></title>
    <link href="http://finatra.info/finatra/blog/2015/10/01/finatra-2-dot-1-0-now-publicly-available/"/>
    <updated>2015-10-01T10:50:53-07:00</updated>
    <id>http://finatra.info/finatra/blog/2015/10/01/finatra-2-dot-1-0-now-publicly-available</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3>We&rsquo;re very happy to announce the <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/releases/tag/v2.1.0">release</a>  of Finatra 2.1.0!</h3>

<p>There are several improvements and features in this release:</p>

<ul>
<li>the ability to &ldquo;disable&rdquo; the <a href="http://twitter.github.io/twitter-server/Features.html#http-admin-interface">TwitterServer HTTP Admin Interface</a> for deploying to environments that only allow binding to a <em>single</em> port for your application.</li>
<li>the ability to &ldquo;turn-off&rdquo; automatic JSON body parsing into a case class for requests that represent JSON blobs (useful for document stores).</li>
<li><p>Closed issues and pull-requests:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/228">https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/228</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/253">https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/253</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/255">https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/255</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/issues/257">https://github.com/twitter/finatra/issues/257</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/258">https://github.com/twitter/finatra/pull/258</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>


<p>You can download the release from <a href="http://search.maven.org/#search%7Cga%7C1%7Cg%3A%22com.twitter.finatra%22%20AND%20v%3A%222.1.0%22">Maven Central</a>.</p>

<p>For a full list of changes and updates from the previous version, see the diff <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/compare/v2.0.1...v2.1.0">here</a>.</p>

<p>See the Finatra <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra">github page</a> for more information on getting started.</p>

<p>&ndash; The <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/finatra-users">Finatra</a> Team</p>
]]></content>
  </entry>
  
