    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Finatra 1.5.1 Released]]></title>
    <link href="http://finatra.info/finatra/blog/2014/01/13/finatra-1-dot-5-1-released/"/>
    <updated>2014-01-13T08:29:18-08:00</updated>
    <id>http://finatra.info/finatra/blog/2014/01/13/finatra-1-dot-5-1-released</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3>Response internals fix</h3>

<p><p class="lead">
It is now possible to modify the response &ldquo;out of band&rdquo;, since <code>Response</code> is tied to <code>Request</code> via <code>request.response</code>. For example, in a filter:</p>

<p><pre class="prettyprint">
class ExampleFilter
  extends SimpleFilter[Request, Response] {</p>

<p>  def apply(
    request: FinagleRequest,
    service: Service[Request, Response])
  ) = {
    request.response.headers.add(&ldquo;X-Filtered&rdquo;, &ldquo;True&rdquo;)
    service(request)
  }</p>

<p>}
</pre></p>

<p><p class="lead">
See <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/blob/1.5.1/src/test/scala/com/twitter/finatra/RequestResponseSpec.scala">RequestResponseSpec</a> for more details.</p>

<p><br/></p>

<h3>Changelog</h3>

<p><p class="lead">
<a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/commit/75ebe3c23678bba40cff0493b7f9806cf27de883">75ebe3</a> Correctly set Content-Length for unicode JSON responses</p>

<p><p class="lead">
<a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/commit/1459817858f6dea218ab7de4861b3bba14ccadbc">145981</a> Depend on finagle-stats, fixes <a href="https://github.com/twitter/finatra/issues/95">#95</a></p>

